<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued January 27 at 4:05PM EST until further notice by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 445 PM EST
FOR EAST CENTRAL FAIRFIELD AND WEST CENTRAL KERSHAW COUNTIES...
At 405 PM EST, a severe thunderstorm was located near Longtown, or
near Lake Wateree Dam, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and powerlines.
Locations impacted include...
Lake Wateree Dam and Longtown.
TORNADO...POSSIBLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
